documentation.value:
Inserts element `value` at position `pos` in `list`, shifting up other elements. The default value for `pos` is `#list+1` (append).

```lua
local t = {1, 2, 3}
table.insert(t, 4)       -- {1, 2, 3, 4}
table.insert(t, 2, 10)   -- {1, 10, 2, 3, 4}
```

Removes from `list` the element at position `pos`, returning the removed value. Default `pos` is `#list` (last element).

```lua
local t = {1, 2, 3, 4}
local v = table.remove(t)     -- v=4, t={1,2,3}
local w = table.remove(t, 1)  -- w=1, t={2,3}
```

Sorts the list elements in-place, from `list[1]` to `list[#list]`. An optional comparison function `comp` can be provided.

```lua
local t = {3, 1, 4, 1, 5}
table.sort(t)  -- {1, 1, 3, 4, 5}
table.sort(t, function(a, b) return a > b end)  -- descending
```

Moves elements from table `a1` to table `a2`. Equivalent to `a2[t], ... = a1[f], ..., a1[e]` with appropriate destination indexing. Returns `a2`.

```lua
local t = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5}
table.move(t, 3, 5, 1)  -- {3, 4, 5, 4, 5}
```

**Note:** Available in Lua 5.3+ only.

